============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is the Big Bang?
A1: The Big Bang theory states the universe began from an
     extremely hot, dense point approximately 13.8 billion
     years ago and has been expanding ever since.

Q2: What is evolution?
A2: Evolution by natural selection: organisms with
     beneficial traits reproduce more, passing traits to
     offspring. Over generations, populations change. Darwin
     proposed this in 1859.

Q3: What is entropy?
A3: Entropy measures disorder or randomness in a system.
     The Second Law of Thermodynamics states it always
     increases in isolated systems — the arrow of time.

Q4: What is an algorithm?
A4: An algorithm is a step-by-step procedure for solving a
     problem. Algorithms have inputs, defined steps, and
     outputs. Examples: sorting, searching, path-finding.

Q5: What is relativity?
A5: Einstein's relativity: Special (1905) — time dilates,
     mass increases at high speeds; E=mc². General (1915) —
     gravity is curved spacetime; explains black holes and
     expanding universe.

